      <div class="card pageCard">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div id="personaldata" class="anchor"></div>
          <h2 class="card-title">
            What personal data we collect
          </h2>
          <p class="card-text">
            Sir Stratalot may collect and use the following kinds of personal data:
          </p>
          <ul class="card-text">
            <li><strong>Log data.</strong> When you visit our website, our servers may automatically log the standard data provided by your web browser. It may include your computer’s Internet Protocol (IP) address, your browser type and version, the pages you visit, the time and date of your visit, the time spent on each page, and other details. We don’t use this data to identifiably associate you with your site visits or usage.</li>
            <li><strong>Data from third parties.</strong> If you sign in to Sir Stratalot with Twitter, we save some publicly visible info from your Twitter profile: your Twitter ID, display name, and username—as well as your bio, URL, and avatar image URL if you’ve set those. We don’t collect any other data from Twitter, nor will we ever post to your Twitter account.</li>
            <li><strong>Data you generate while using the site.</strong> By interacting with Sir Stratalot while signed in with Twitter, you may generate data about your interactions that we save and associate with your Sir Stratalot account. Specifically, we store what links you’ve ‘liked’ and any links you submit.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card pageCard">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div id="legalbases" class="anchor"></div>
          <h2 class="card-title">
            Legal bases for processing
          </h2>
          <p class="card-text">
            We will process your personal information lawfully, fairly and in a transparent manner. We collect and process information about you only where we have legal bases for doing so. These legal bases depend on the services you use and how you use them, meaning we collect and use your information only where:
          </p>
          <ul class="card-text">
            <li>it’s necessary for the performance of a contract to which you are a party or to take steps at your request before entering into such a contract (for example, when we provide a service you request from us);</li>
            <li>it satisfies a legitimate interest (which is not overridden by your data protection interests), such as for research and development, to market and promote our services, and to protect our legal rights and interests;</li> 
            <li>you give us consent to do so for a specific purpose (for example, you might consent to us sending you our newsletter); or</li> 
            <li>we need to process your data to comply with a legal obligation.</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="card-text">
            Where you consent to our use of information about you for a specific purpose, you have the right to change your mind at any time (but this will not affect any processing that has already taken place).
          </p>
          <p class="card-text">
            We don’t keep personal information for longer than is necessary. While we retain this information, we will protect it within commercially acceptable means to prevent loss and theft, as well as unauthorised access, disclosure, copying, use or modification. That said, we advise that no method of electronic transmission or storage is 100% secure and cannot guarantee absolute data security. If necessary, we may retain your personal information for our compliance with a legal obligation or in order to protect your vital interests or the vital interests of another natural person.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="card pageCard">
        <div class="card-body">
          <div id="datause" class="anchor"></div>
          <h2 class="card-title">
            How we use your personal data
          </h2>
          <p class="card-text">
            We may collect, hold, use and disclose information for the following purposes and personal information will not be further processed in a manner that is incompatible with these purposes:
          </p>
          <ul class="card-text">
            <li>to authenticate you as a user, and enable your access to and use of website services as an authenticated user (by using third party data from Twitter);</li> 
            <li>to enable you to customize or personalize your experience of the website (by using your Sir Stratalot account data and data you generate while signed in).</li>
            <li>to understand how people use the site and how we can improve it (by using automatically collected, non-personally identifiable log data);</li>
            <li>for internal record keeping and administrative purposes;</li>
            <li>to comply with our legal obligations and resolve any disputes that we may have.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
